IDENTIFY AND COMMUNICATE ISSUES ARISING IN THE WORKPLACE
This competency means that the trainer is able to recognize problems or issues that occur during training or in a simulated/workplace
environment and communicate them clearly and professionally to the appropriate people (learners, supervisors, or management)

Key responsibilities of the Trainer
-Identify issues early (observe behavior, performance, end environment)
-Analyze the cause of the problem
-Communicate clearly and calmly
-Use appropriate channels (discussio , report, feedback, session)
-Suggest solutions or corrective actions

Examples:
-Caregiving Training (Safety  Issue)
  >The trainer notices a trainee not following proper handwashing procedures
-Classroom/Workshop Setting (Performance Issue)
  >Some trainees are unable to follow instructions during a practical task
-Group activity (Conflict Issue)
  >Two trainees have a misunderstanding during a team task
  >The trainer identifies that there are not enough tools/equipment for all learners

How to communicate issues Effectively:
-Be clear and specific about the issue
-Focus on the problem, not the person
-Use a respectful and professional tone
-Provide possible solutions
-Encourage feedback and participation


