APPLY ENVIRONMENTAL PRINCIPLES AND ADVOCATE CONSERVATION
This competency means the trainer applies environmental responsible practices in technical training 
and encourages learners to protect and conserve natural resources

Key Focus Areas
-Proper waste secgrgation and disposal
-Energy and water conservation
-Use of environmentally safe materials and methods
-Promoting clean and safe workplace practices
-Encouraging sustainability and environmental responsibility

Examples:
-Care giving training setting
  The trainer teaches learners to properly dispose of medical waste (ex....)
-Workshop or Technical Training (ex...)
  The trainer emphasizes turning off equipment when not in use and properly disposing of used oil, batteries, or electronic waste.
